===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|ss=伩|alt=㐰,孞,𡥪,䚱,訫}}
{{etymon|zh|:der<unc><conj:or>|och:允<tr:*winʔ><t:to trust; to be true>|och:仁<tr:*niŋ><t:kind>|id=true}}
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} reconstructs the {{cog|och|-}} minimally as ''*sin'' and suggests possible derivation from {{och-l|允|tr=*winʔ|to trust; to be true}}.

Alternatively, {{zh-ref|Sagart and Baxter (2012)}} reconstruct ''*s-niŋ-s'' (''*s-ni[ŋ]-s'' in {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}}) and suggest a derivation from {{och-l|仁|tr=*niŋ|kind}} with the prefix ''*s-'', probably used to increase its valency.

